<DESC><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">The United States Section of the International Boundary and Water Commission (USIBWC) is issuing a solicitation (sealed bid) for the purpose of removing sediment in Thurman I Arroyo, Thurman II Arroyo, and a 9,500-linear foot section of the Rio Grande, and to construct sediment basins with erosion protection, concrete end walls, and drilled piers. </span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">The Work for this project generally consists of removal of existing rocks and sediment in Thurman Arroyos I and II within the limits of USIBWC's right of way and construction of dewatering, sedimentation basins, concrete end walls, drilled piers, erosion protection, flex base maintenance road, site grading, and associated drainage improvements. Major tasks include: removal of rocks and sediment from arroyos, installation of sedimentation basins &amp; concrete end walls, drilled piers, and removal of sediment along a 9,500-linear foot stretch from the R